The gas temperature in the “hot” plasma zone is a key parameter concerning ethanol decomposition. The collision rates in the plasma at atmospheric pressure are high enough to ensure local thermodynamic equilibrium. Therefore, the rotational temperature can be taken as a good approximation to the gas kinetic temperature. The emission band from the CN species corresponding to violet CN(B2Σ+→X2Σ+)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
